01:22:13.560 --> 01:22:15.200
A'Court: I DON'T
THINK THERE WOULD BE

01:22:15.200 --> 01:22:18.060
A PLANT ON EARTH THAT
COMES NEAR TO THE AMOUNT

01:22:18.060 --> 01:22:19.430
OF EQUIPMENT AND TECHNOLOGY

01:22:19.430 --> 01:22:22.100
AVAILABLE TO GROW
IT TO ITS POTENTIAL.

01:22:22.100 --> 01:22:24.500
IT'S MORE THAN JUST A HOBBY.

01:22:24.500 --> 01:22:25.960
IT'S A WHOLE LIFE'S WORK.

01:22:25.960 --> 01:22:28.230
SOME PEOPLE -- THAT
IS THEIR WHOLE LIFE.

01:22:28.230 --> 01:22:32.330
THEY'RE SO ENTHUSIASTIC
ABOUT THEIR SO-CALLED HOBBY.

01:22:32.330 --> 01:22:33.500
IT'S UNEXPLAINABLE.

01:22:33.500 --> 01:22:37.660
IT'S NOT JUST SOMETHING
ABOUT DRUGS OR MONEY,

01:22:37.660 --> 01:22:40.860
BUT THERE REALLY IS
A DEEP FASCINATION

01:22:40.860 --> 01:22:44.330
WITH THE MARIJUANA PLANT.

01:22:44.330 --> 01:22:45.900
Pollan: THE WAY I SEE PLANTS,

01:22:45.900 --> 01:22:47.700
THEY'RE JUST AS
ADVANCED AS WE ARE,

01:22:47.700 --> 01:22:51.300
FROM AN EVOLUTIONARY
POINT OF VIEW.

01:22:51.300 --> 01:22:52.560
WHILE WE WERE WORKING ON

01:22:52.560 --> 01:22:54.630
CONSCIOUSNESS,
LANGUAGE, TOOL-MAKING,

01:22:54.630 --> 01:22:58.400
ALL THESE THINGS WE JUDGE TO
BE SO WONDERFUL AND IMPORTANT,

01:22:58.400 --> 01:23:00.860
THEY WERE WORKING
ON DIFFERENT TOOLS.

01:23:00.860 --> 01:23:04.260
AND THEIR TOOLS ARE JUST
AS SOPHISTICATED AS OURS.

01:23:04.260 --> 01:23:08.930
THE FACT THAT THIS PLANT,
CANNABIS, FOR EXAMPLE,

01:23:08.930 --> 01:23:13.200
CAN ACTUALLY CHANGE THE TEXTURE
OF CONSCIOUSNESS -- YOU KNOW,

01:23:13.200 --> 01:23:16.400
THIS IS INGENIOUS.

01:23:16.400 --> 01:23:19.030
WE WOULD NOT BE THE SAME,
IF NOT FOR CANNABIS.

01:23:19.030 --> 01:23:21.630
AND CANNABIS CERTAINLY
IS VERY DIFFERENT

01:23:21.630 --> 01:23:23.200
FOR ITS RELATIONSHIP WITH US.

01:23:23.200 --> 01:23:46.730
IT'S ONE OF THE GREAT WINNERS
IN THIS DANCE OF DOMESTICATION.

01:23:46.730 --> 01:23:49.300
McDormand: LOOKING DOWN
AT IT FROM THE AIR,

01:23:49.300 --> 01:23:53.100
YOU MIGHT NOT GUESS THAT
SOUTHERN IDAHO IS A DESERT.

01:23:53.100 --> 01:23:57.330
THE BIG GREEN CIRCLES
ARE CROP FIELDS.

01:23:57.330 --> 01:24:00.560
THEY GET THEIR WATER FROM
A VAST IRRIGATION SYSTEM

01:24:00.560 --> 01:24:06.700
OF UNDERGROUND PIPES
AND GIANT SPRINKLERS.

01:24:06.700 --> 01:24:10.030
THIS IS ONE OF THE MOST
PRODUCTIVE FARM AREAS

01:24:10.030 --> 01:24:12.130
IN THE UNITED STATES,

01:24:12.130 --> 01:24:13.530
AND ONE OF THE PRINCIPAL SOURCES

01:24:13.530 --> 01:24:17.430
OF A FOOD CROP THAT FEEDS
MILLIONS OF PEOPLE --

01:24:17.430 --> 01:24:20.000
THE POTATO.

01:24:20.000 --> 01:24:23.300
Pollan: THE DESIRE, I
THINK, THAT THE POTATO

01:24:23.300 --> 01:24:25.230
HAS EVOLVED TO
GRATIFY, IN LARGE PART,

01:24:25.230 --> 01:24:29.100
IS OUR DESIRE FOR CONTROL
-- CONTROL OVER OUR FATE.

01:24:29.100 --> 01:24:31.630
IT GIVES US THAT BY PROVIDING

01:24:31.630 --> 01:24:35.230
AN IMMENSE AMOUNT
OF FOOD PER ACRE.

01:24:35.230 --> 01:24:38.830
AN INDIVIDUAL WITH HALF
AN ACRE OF POTATOES

01:24:38.830 --> 01:24:41.060
CAN GROW ENOUGH FOOD
TO KEEP HIMSELF ALIVE

01:24:41.060 --> 01:24:45.530
OR HIS FAMILY ALIVE FOR A YEAR.

01:24:45.530 --> 01:24:48.200
IT'S KIND OF EXTRAORDINARY.

01:24:48.200 --> 01:24:51.060
Man: WHEN YOU LIFT UP THE
SOIL AND YOU SEE THESE

01:24:51.060 --> 01:24:53.160
BEAUTIFUL POTATOES
THAT ARE SO NUTRITIOUS

01:24:53.160 --> 01:24:56.500
GROWING UNDERNEATH THEM, IT'S
JUST -- IT'S REALLY, YOU KNOW,

01:24:56.500 --> 01:25:00.960
EXCITING TO SEE HOW PRODUCTIVE
AND HOW AMAZING THIS CROP IS,

01:25:00.960 --> 01:25:03.500
THAT IT CAN TAKE THIS
LITTLE TINY PLANT

01:25:03.500 --> 01:25:04.860
AND PRODUCE THIS GREAT FOOD.

01:25:04.860 --> 01:25:08.130
Pollan: THE STORY THAT
WE'VE BEEN TELLING SO FAR

01:25:08.130 --> 01:25:11.330
IS THE STORY OF THE
SYMBIOTIC RELATIONSHIP

01:25:11.330 --> 01:25:14.160
BUT WITH THE POTATO, WE ENTER

01:25:14.160 --> 01:25:16.960
INTO A VERY NEW CHAPTER
IN THAT RELATIONSHIP --

01:25:16.960 --> 01:25:19.200
THE GENETIC
MODIFICATION OF PLANTS.

01:25:19.200 --> 01:25:23.560
FOR THE FIRST
TIME, WE ARE TAKING

01:25:23.560 --> 01:25:25.860
GENES FROM ONE DISTANT SPECIES

01:25:25.860 --> 01:25:29.260
AND INTRODUCING IT INTO ANOTHER.

01:25:29.260 --> 01:25:31.560
THAT REPRESENTS A
REAL QUANTUM CHANGE

01:25:31.560 --> 01:25:33.430
IN OUR RELATIONSHIP TO PLANTS.

01:25:33.430 --> 01:25:37.330
