AND, YOU KNOW,
IT'S EASY FOR US

01:39:56.130 --> 01:39:58.460
TO SIT HERE AND CRITICIZE
THEM FOR SPRAYING

01:39:58.460 --> 01:40:00.500
THESE CHEMICALS ON OUR
FOOD, BUT THE FACT IS,

01:40:00.500 --> 01:40:03.830
IF THEY WERE TO GIVE UP
ON A SINGLE SPRAYING,

01:40:03.830 --> 01:40:07.400
McDormand: IN 1995, RYAN
CRANNEY AND FARMERS LIKE HIM

01:40:07.400 --> 01:40:10.760
WELCOMED THE NEWS OF AN
AGRICULTURAL BREAKTHROUGH

01:40:10.760 --> 01:40:13.730
THAT PROMISED TO CUT
DOWN THEIR USE OF SPRAYS.

01:40:13.730 --> 01:40:18.330
MONSANTO, THE WORLD'S BIGGEST
BIOTECHNOLOGY COMPANY,

01:40:18.330 --> 01:40:20.300
CAME UP WITH A MUCH
LESS TOXIC METHOD

01:40:20.300 --> 01:40:23.930
FOR KILLING ONE OF THE POTATO'S
MOST DEADLY ENEMIES --

01:40:23.930 --> 01:40:25.930
THE COLORADO POTATO BEETLE,

01:40:25.930 --> 01:40:29.530
WHICH CAN PICK THE
LEAVES OFF A PLANT

01:40:29.530 --> 01:40:31.330
VIRTUALLY OVERNIGHT.

01:40:31.330 --> 01:40:31.360
Thornton: COLORADO
POTATO BEETLE,

01:40:31.360 --> 01:40:32.600
Thornton: COLORADO
POTATO BEETLE,

01:40:32.600 --> 01:40:38.060
WORLDWIDE, IS PROBABLY
THE MOST SERIOUS INSECT
PEST IN POTATOES.

01:40:38.060 --> 01:40:40.760
WE STILL ESTIMATE
THAT, YOU KNOW,

01:40:40.760 --> 01:40:42.700
AND PROBABLY ACROSS
THE U.S. AS A WHOLE,

01:40:42.700 --> 01:40:45.960
ABOUT 40% OF THE INSECTICIDES
THAT WERE APPLIED

01:40:45.960 --> 01:40:49.360
WERE APPLIED FOR COLORADO
POTATO BEETLE CONTROL.

01:40:49.360 --> 01:40:52.900
McDormand: MONSANTO'S
INNOVATION WAS TO CREATE

01:40:52.900 --> 01:40:56.600
A NEW KIND OF POTATO,
CALLED THE NewLeaf POTATO.

01:40:56.600 --> 01:41:00.600
IT WAS THE FIRST POTATO TO
BE GENETICALLY ENGINEERED

01:41:00.600 --> 01:41:04.660
TO CONTAIN GENES FROM A
DIFFERENT BIOLOGICAL SPECIES.

01:41:04.660 --> 01:41:09.400
Woman: GENETIC ENGINEERING IS
A RADICALLY NEW TECHNOLOGY,

01:41:09.400 --> 01:41:13.330
COMPARED TO
TRADITIONAL BREEDING.

01:41:13.330 --> 01:41:16.130
IT ALLOWS US TO MOVE GENES

01:41:16.130 --> 01:41:19.100
WITHOUT REGARD TO
SPECIES BARRIERS.

01:41:19.100 --> 01:41:24.330
IT ALLOWS US TO MOVE A
GENE FROM A BUTTERFLY,

01:41:24.330 --> 01:41:25.460
YOU KNOW, INTO A CORN PLANT,

01:41:25.460 --> 01:41:28.100
FROM A STARFISH
INTO A WHEAT PLANT.

01:41:28.100 --> 01:41:31.900
McDormand: MONSANTO'S
NewLeaf POTATO USED A GENE

01:41:31.900 --> 01:41:33.500
FROM A COMMON SOIL BACTERIUM,

01:41:33.500 --> 01:41:37.060
ONE THAT MAKES A PROTEIN
THAT KILLS POTATO BEETLES

01:41:37.060 --> 01:41:38.860
WITHOUT CAUSING HARM TO HUMANS.

01:41:38.860 --> 01:41:44.060
THE BACTERIUM IS CALLED
BACILLUS THURINGIENSIS,

01:41:44.060 --> 01:41:46.530
OR Bt FOR SHORT.

01:41:46.530 --> 01:41:48.200
TO HELP MARKET ITS Bt POTATO,

01:41:48.200 --> 01:41:52.060
MONSANTO HIRED PLANT
PHYSIOLOGIST MICHAEL THORNTON

01:41:52.060 --> 01:41:55.460
TO BE ONE OF ITS LIAISONS
TO FARMERS IN IDAHO.

01:41:55.460 --> 01:41:58.260
Thornton: MONSANTO
WAS ABLE TO IDENTIFY

01:41:58.260 --> 01:42:00.800
THE GENE IN THAT
BACTERIUM, THE Bt GENE

01:42:00.800 --> 01:42:04.060
THAT WAS RESPONSIBLE FOR
PRODUCTION OF THAT PROTEIN.

01:42:04.060 --> 01:42:07.600
AND THEY COULD USE A
PROCESS TO INSERT THAT GENE

01:42:07.600 --> 01:42:10.600
INTO A POTATO VARIETY,
ONE THAT GROWERS

01:42:10.600 --> 01:42:12.560
WERE ALREADY FAMILIAR WITH.

01:42:12.560 --> 01:42:14.830
THE BEETLE EATS THAT LEAF

01:42:14.830 --> 01:42:18.260
AND GETS THAT Bt
PROTEIN INSIDE IT

01:42:18.260 --> 01:42:21.360
AND IT DISRUPTS ITS
DIGESTIVE SYSTEM,

01:42:21.360 --> 01:42:25.330
AND THAT EVENTUALLY KILLS
THE COLORADO POTATO BEETLE.

01:42:25.330 --> 01:42:29.360
I CAME FROM THE STANDPOINT THAT
TECHNOLOGY AND NEW IMPROVEMENTS

01:42:29.360 --> 01:42:31.700
WERE A GOOD THING FOR
THE POTATO INDUSTRY,

01:42:31.700 --> 01:42:34.330
SO I WAS VERY EXCITED TO
SEE SOMETHING THAT WAS

01:42:34.330 --> 01:42:37.830
KIND OF A QUANTUM LEAP IN
TECHNOLOGY FOR THE INDUSTRY

01:42:37.830 --> 01:42:38.730
BE INTRODUCED.

01:42:38.730 --> 01:42:40.100
Pollan: THE PROMISE HERE WAS

01:42:40.100 --> 01:42:41.300
THAT YOU COULD
DIMINISH SPRAYING.

01:42:41.300 --> 01:42:44.060
YOU MIGHT PAY A LITTLE BIT
MORE FOR THESE POTATOES,

01:42:44.060 --> 01:42:46.930
BUT SINCE THEY GENERATED
THEIR OWN PESTICIDE,

01:42:46.930 --> 01:42:48.330
YOU COULD GIVE UP SOME
OF YOUR SPRAYINGS.

01:42:48.330 --> 01:42:54.100
AND THIS WAS VERY ATTRACTIVE
TO A LOT OF POTATO FARMERS.

01:42:54.100 --> 01:42:55.860
AND THOUGHT THAT IT WAS
REALLY GOING TO TAKE OFF.

01:42:55.860 --> 01:43:02.160
McDormand: IN 1996, THE NewLeaf
POTATO BEGAN MAKING ITS WAY

01:43:02.160 --> 01:43:05.230
INTO FAST FOOD CHAINS
AND SUPERMARKETS.

01:43:05.230 --> 01:43:08.260
AS TIME WENT BY,
MILLIONS OF PEOPLE

01:43:08.260 --> 01:43:11.160
WERE EATING THE GENETICALLY
MODIFIED POTATOES,

01:43:11.160 --> 01:43:13.430
BUT HARDLY ANY OF
THEM REALIZED IT,

01:43:13.430 --> 01:43:15.000
BECAUSE THE GOVERNMENT HAD RULED

01:43:15.000 --> 01:43:16.860
THE POTATOES DIDN'T
NEED TO BE LABELED.

01:43:16.860 --> 01:43:20.700
Pollan: I REALIZED AS
I DID MY REPORTING,

01:43:20.700 --> 01:43:23.330
I'D BEEN IN A McDONALD'S.
I'D BOUGHT FRITO-LAY CHIPS.

01:43:23.330 --> 01:43:26.230
AND THE THING I LEARNED
THAT I HADN'T BEEN AWARE OF,

01:43:26.230 --> 01:43:28.300
BECAUSE WE HADN'T BEEN
TOLD, IS THAT WE AMERICANS

01:43:28.300 --> 01:43:31.460
HAD BEEN EATING THESE POTATOES
ALREADY FOR A COUPLE OF YEARS.

01:43:31.460 --> 01:43:34.430
Thornton: THE POTATO WAS
THE SAME, NUTRITIONALLY,

01:43:34.430 --> 01:43:37.700
HAD THE SAME LEVEL OF
VITAMINS, THINGS LIKE THAT.

01:43:37.700 --> 01:43:40.600
IT JUST HAD THIS ONE
ADDITIONAL GENE THAT CODES

01:43:40.600 --> 01:43:44.430
FOR A PROTEIN THAT MAKES UP LESS
THAN A TENTH OF ONE-PERCENT

01:43:44.430 --> 01:43:46.930
OF THE TOTAL PROTEIN
IN THE PLANT.

01:43:46.930 --> 01:43:48.130
AND THE DECISION BY

01:43:48.130 --> 01:43:51.560
THE FOOD AND DRUG
ADMINISTRATION WAS THAT,

01:43:51.560 --> 01:43:54.560
UNLESS IT'S SUBSTANTIALLY
DIFFERENT --

01:43:54.560 --> 01:43:57.100
UNLESS YOU'VE CHANGED
THE NUTRIENT PROFILE --

01:43:57.100 --> 01:44:01.500
IT DOES NOT NEED TO BE LABELED.

01:44:01.500 --> 01:44:04.230
NOW, IT SEEMS TO
ME THAT THE POTATO

01:44:04.230 --> 01:44:07.000
NEVER BEFORE PRODUCED
THIS PESTICIDE.

01:44:07.000 --> 01:44:09.600
SO TO SAY THAT POTATOES
PRODUCING PESTICIDE

01:44:09.600 --> 01:44:12.760
ARE SUBSTANTIALLY EQUIVALENT
TO POTATOES THAT DON'T

01:44:12.760 --> 01:44:17.030
SEEMS TO INVOLVE A CERTAIN
SUSPENSION OF DISBELIEF.

01:44:17.030 --> 01:44:19.030
HEY, HEY! HO, HO!

01:44:19.030 --> 01:44:21.630
WE DON'T WANT NO
GMOs! HEY, HEY!

01:44:21.630 --> 01:44:24.060
McDormand: IN THE LATE
1990s, AS THE NewLeaf

01:44:24.060 --> 01:44:26.360
WAS MAKING INROADS
INTO THE MARKET,

01:44:26.360 --> 01:44:29.730
THE ISSUE OF GENETICALLY
MODIFIED ORGANISMS, OR GMOs,

01:44:29.730 --> 01:44:33.560
WAS AROUSING INTENSE
OPPOSITION ALL OVER THE WORLD.

01:44:33.560 --> 01:44:35.600
WE DON'T WANT NO GMO!

01:44:35.600 --> 01:44:37.160
HEY, HEY! HO, HO!

01:44:37.160 --> 01:44:39.200
Man: I WANT TO KNOW
WHAT'S GOING ON

01:44:39.200 --> 01:44:41.130
IN MY BODY AND MY
DAUGHTER'S BODY

01:44:41.130 --> 01:44:43.460
WHEN THEY FEED CORN TO -- TO US

01:44:43.460 --> 01:44:45.700
THAT'S BEEN GENETICALLY ALTERED.

01:44:45.700 --> 01:44:47.860
THEY DON'T KNOW.
THEY CAN'T TELL YOU.

01:44:47.860 --> 01:44:49.430
WHAT DO WE WANT? SAFE FOOD!

01:44:49.430 --> 01:44:50.700
WHEN DO WE WANT IT? NOW!

01:44:50.700 --> 01:44:53.130
Mellon: THE Bt
POTATO OFFERS FARMERS

01:44:53.130 --> 01:44:53.160
REDUCED COST.

01:44:53.160 --> 01:44:53.930
REDUCED COST.

01:44:53.930 --> 01:44:56.630
IT DOESN'T OFFER
CONSUMERS ANYTHING.

01:44:56.630 --> 01:45:01.600
AND SO A LOT OF CONSUMERS,
IF THEY WERE GIVEN A CHOICE,

01:45:01.600 --> 01:45:06.800
MIGHT SAY, WELL, IT DOESN'T
PROVIDE AN ADVANTAGE FOR ME.

01:45:06.800 --> 01:45:09.960
AND THEREFORE, NOT KNOWING
A WHOLE LOT ABOUT IT,

01:45:09.960 --> 01:45:14.960
I MIGHT -- I MIGHT
SIMPLY SAY NO.

01:45:14.960 --> 01:45:16.860
Pollan: I DO KNOW
McDONALD'S WAS GETTING

01:45:16.860 --> 01:45:19.060
A CERTAIN NUMBER OF CALLS
AND LETTERS ASKING THEM,

01:45:19.060 --> 01:45:24.530
IS IT TRUE THAT YOU
ARE SERVING GENETICALLY
MODIFIED POTATOES?

01:45:24.530 --> 01:45:26.660
THIS IS A COMPANY, LIKE
MANY FOOD COMPANIES,

01:45:26.660 --> 01:45:28.830
EXQUISITELY SENSITIVE
TO PUBLIC OPINION.

01:45:28.830 --> 01:45:31.260
AND THEY PROBABLY
SAW A POTENTIAL

01:45:31.260 --> 01:45:35.030
PRUIN MONSANTO'S BUSINESS,
THEY DIDN'T WANT TO, YOU KNOW,

01:45:35.030 --> 01:45:38.160
BUT THEY VERY QUIETLY SAID
THAT AFTER THE FOLLOWING YEAR,

01:45:38.160 --> 01:45:41.260
THEY WOULD NO LONGER
BE TAKING THEM.

01:45:41.260 --> 01:45:45.100
AND WITH THAT, THE
NewLeaf POTATO WAS OVER.

01:45:45.100 --> 01:45:49.030
McDormand: IN 2001,
MONSANTO STOPPED SELLING

01:45:49.030 --> 01:45:50.060
THE NewLeaf POTATO.

01:45:50.060 --> 01:45:53.500
IT HAD CAPTURED ONLY
ABOUT 5% OF THE MARKET.

01:45:53.500 --> 01:45:55.830
BOTH McDONALD'S AND MONSANTO

01:45:55.830 --> 01:46:00.160
DECLINED TO BE INTERVIEWED
FOR THIS PROGRAM.

01:46:00.160 --> 01:46:02.930
Thornton: I WAS VERY
DISAPPOINTED -- TO SEE

01:46:02.930 --> 01:46:05.800
THIS WHOLE DREAM JUST
KIND OF BEING SHUT DOWN

01:46:05.800 --> 01:46:08.830
OVER RELATIVELY A
SHORT PERIOD OF TIME

