SEEMED TO ME TO BE A TRAGEDY.

01:46:11.800 --> 01:46:13.100
I DON'T THINK IT WAS A TRAGEDY.

01:46:13.100 --> 01:46:16.260
I THINK IT WAS PART
OF A VERY LARGE DEBATE

01:46:16.260 --> 01:46:20.000
ABOUT HOW OUR SOCIETY
OUGHT TO RESPOND TO THE USE

01:46:20.000 --> 01:46:25.530
OF A RADICALLY NEW TECHNOLOGY
LIKE GENETIC ENGINEERING

01:46:25.530 --> 01:46:30.060
McDormand: BUT SINCE THE
DEMISE OF THE Bt POTATO,

01:46:30.060 --> 01:46:31.760
MONSANTO HAS BEEN
VERY SUCCESSFUL

01:46:31.760 --> 01:46:34.900
SELLING OTHER GENETICALLY
ENGINEERED CROPS --

01:46:34.900 --> 01:46:38.730
LIKE CORN, SOYBEANS,
AND COTTON.

01:46:38.730 --> 01:46:42.730
ENTOMOLOGIST BRUCE
TABASHNIK HAS BEEN STUDYING

01:46:42.730 --> 01:46:45.130
THE Bt COTTON CROP IN ARIZONA.

01:46:45.130 --> 01:46:49.630
Man: WE'RE IN A SPECIAL
SITUATION IN ARIZONA RIGHT NOW

01:46:49.630 --> 01:46:56.430
WHERE ABOUT 98% OF THE
COTTON GROWN IS Bt COTTON.

01:46:56.430 --> 01:47:00.500
IT'S BEING USED AS PART
OF A PROGRAM TO ERADICATE,

01:47:00.500 --> 01:47:04.560
OR AT LEAST GREATLY
SUPPRESS, PINK BOLLWORM.

01:47:04.560 --> 01:47:07.200
McDormand: THE BOLLWORM
IS AS DANGEROUS

01:47:07.200 --> 01:47:10.500
TO THE COTTON CROP AS
THE COLORADO BEETLE

01:47:10.500 --> 01:47:11.760
IS TO POTATOES.

01:47:11.760 --> 01:47:15.100
WE HAVE LOTS OF DAMAGE
INSIDE THE BOLL HERE.

01:47:15.100 --> 01:47:18.600
ONE OR MORE CATERPILLARS
HAS BEEN FEEDING

01:47:18.600 --> 01:47:20.830
ON THE SEEDS INSIDE THE BOLL,

01:47:20.830 --> 01:47:23.360
WHICH IS GREAT
FOR THE INSECTS,

01:47:23.360 --> 01:47:27.800
BUT NOT GOOD FOR THE
PLANT OR FOR THE FARMER.

01:47:27.800 --> 01:47:30.760
McDormand: TABASHNIK
HAS BEEN INVESTIGATING

01:47:30.760 --> 01:47:33.360
ONE OF THE MAJOR CONCERNS
ABOUT Bt CROPS --

01:47:33.360 --> 01:47:37.430
THE DEGREE TO WHICH
INSECTS EVOLVE RESISTANCE

01:47:37.430 --> 01:47:39.700
TO THE BUG-KILLING PROTEIN.

01:47:39.700 --> 01:47:42.630
SOME OF HIS WORK IS PARTLY
FUNDED BY MONSANTO,

01:47:42.630 --> 01:47:47.730
WHICH IS LEGALLY REQUIRED
TO MONITOR Bt RESISTANCE.

01:47:47.730 --> 01:47:51.830
FOR YEARS, ORGANIC FARMERS
HAVE CONTROLLED PESTS

01:47:51.830 --> 01:47:53.130
WITH A SPRAY FORM OF Bt.

01:47:53.130 --> 01:47:55.630
BUT NOW THAT Bt
HAS BEEN ENGINEERED

01:47:55.630 --> 01:48:00.130
INTO CROPS, EXPOSING
INSECTS DAY IN AND DAY OUT,

01:48:00.130 --> 01:48:02.330
TABASHNIK HAS
FOUND THAT THE BUGS

01:48:02.330 --> 01:48:04.900
ARE MORE LIKELY TO
DEVELOP RESISTANCE.

01:48:04.900 --> 01:48:06.360
Tabashnik: IN THE DECADES OF USE

01:48:06.360 --> 01:48:13.160
OF Bt SPRAYS, THERE'S ONLY ONE
INSECT THAT EVOLVED RESISTANCE.

01:48:13.160 --> 01:48:18.530
ON THE OTHER HAND, AFTER ABOUT
A DOZEN YEARS OF Bt CROPS,

01:48:18.530 --> 01:48:20.600
WE ALREADY HAVE THREE EXAMPLES

01:48:20.600 --> 01:48:24.160
OF INSECTS THAT HAVE
EVOLVED RESISTANCE.

01:48:24.160 --> 01:48:26.760
McDormand: BUT
TABASHNIK STILL THINKS

01:48:26.760 --> 01:48:28.030
GENETICALLY ENGINEERED CROPS

01:48:28.030 --> 01:48:31.060
DO MORE TO HELP THE
ENVIRONMENT THAN TO HARM IT.

01:48:31.060 --> 01:48:32.830
Tabashnik: I THINK
THAT ULTIMATELY

