USING TOXIC CHEMICALS.

01:50:31.260 --> 01:50:35.930
Heath: THE CONVENTIONAL
FARMERS CERTAINLY

01:50:35.930 --> 01:50:37.860
KNOW HOW TO FARM WITH CHEMICALS.

01:50:37.860 --> 01:50:41.660
I -- I MYSELF, IF I
HAD TO GO BACK TO THAT,

01:50:41.660 --> 01:50:42.830
I'D -- I WOULD QUIT.

01:50:42.830 --> 01:50:47.530
McDormand: HEATH'S
LABOR COSTS ARE HIGH.

01:50:47.530 --> 01:50:49.460
HE DOESN'T CULTIVATE
AS MANY ACRES

01:50:49.460 --> 01:50:51.160
OR GROW AS MUCH FOOD
AS THE CRANNEYS.

01:50:51.160 --> 01:50:55.200
BUT SINCE HE SPENDS NEXT
TO NOTHING ON PESTICIDES

01:50:55.200 --> 01:50:58.460
AND GETS GOOD PRICES
FOR HIS ORGANIC POTATOES

01:50:58.460 --> 01:50:59.530
IN SPECIALTY MARKETS,

01:50:59.530 --> 01:51:01.830
HE USUALLY EARNS
MORE MONEY PER ACRE.

01:51:01.830 --> 01:51:03.830
Heath: I USED TO BE
REALLY PRETTY STUPID,

01:51:03.830 --> 01:51:08.000
YOU KNOW, AS
FAR AS MY NEIGHBORS WERE
CONCERNED, PRETTY SILLY.

01:51:08.000 --> 01:51:11.230
BUT I HAVE A LOT
MORE RESPECT NOW

01:51:11.230 --> 01:51:14.430
THAN I DID 10, 15 YEARS AGO.

01:51:14.430 --> 01:51:16.430
THEY CAN SEE THAT I'M
STILL IN BUSINESS,

01:51:16.430 --> 01:51:18.760
AND WE'VE GOT GOOD MARKETS,

01:51:18.760 --> 01:51:19.830
AND WE GROW A GOOD PRODUCT,

01:51:19.830 --> 01:51:22.130
AND I'M PROUD TO BE
AN ORGANIC FARMER.

01:51:22.130 --> 01:51:26.060
Pollan: YOU KNOW, THERE ARE
OTHER WAYS TO SKIN A CAT.

01:51:26.060 --> 01:51:28.160
AND FARMERS ARE FIGURING IT OUT.

01:51:28.160 --> 01:51:29.600
AND THEY'RE FIGURING OUT

01:51:29.600 --> 01:51:32.130
HOW TO GROW FOOD
WITHOUT PESTICIDES,

01:51:32.130 --> 01:51:34.560
AND THE KEY -- THE KEY
INSIGHT THAT YOU FIND

01:51:34.560 --> 01:51:38.230
IN ALL THE CREATIVE FARMERS
WHO HAVE SOLVED THIS PROBLEM

01:51:38.230 --> 01:51:40.130
IS GETTING AWAY
FROM MONOCULTURE.

01:51:40.130 --> 01:51:43.300
THE ANSWER TO THE
PROBLEMS OF MONOCULTURE

01:51:43.300 --> 01:51:46.860
IS NOT NEW TECHNOLOGIES,
IT'S NOT BAND-AIDS.

01:51:46.860 --> 01:51:50.930
IT'S GETTING AWAY
FROM MONOCULTURE.

01:51:50.930 --> 01:51:53.630
Mellon: I THINK
IF WE COULD LEARN

01:51:53.630 --> 01:51:56.860
FROM THE PERUVIANS,
IF WE COULD STEP BACK

01:51:56.860 --> 01:52:00.660
AND APPRECIATE THE DIVERSITY
THAT THEY'VE GIVEN US

01:52:00.660 --> 01:52:01.700
IN THE POTATO

01:52:01.700 --> 01:52:06.000
AND TAKE ADVANTAGE OF
IT IN OUR AGRICULTURE,

01:52:06.000 --> 01:52:08.200
THAT IS THE WAY FORWARD.

01:52:08.200 --> 01:52:09.760
Thornton: I THINK
SOME OF THE METHODS

01:52:09.760 --> 01:52:13.060
THEY'VE DEVELOPED IN PERU
TO USE GENETIC DIVERSITY

01:52:13.060 --> 01:52:17.500
BY PLANTING A WHOLE RANGE OF
VARIETIES WITHIN ONE FIELD

01:52:17.500 --> 01:52:18.760
IS A VERY GOOD STRATEGY,

01:52:18.760 --> 01:52:22.600
BUT I JUST DON'T SEE HOW
WE READILY ADAPT THAT

01:52:22.600 --> 01:52:25.530
TO A PRODUCTION
SYSTEM THAT NOT ONLY

01:52:25.530 --> 01:52:28.130
HAS TO FEED PEOPLE
IN THE U.S.,

01:52:28.130 --> 01:52:29.630
BUT FEED A WORLDWIDE POPULATION

01:52:29.630 --> 01:52:31.960
WITH A PRODUCT THAT'S
A CERTAIN QUALITY.

01:52:31.960 --> 01:52:35.700
Pollan: THE ORDER
WE IMPOSE ON NATURE

01:52:35.700 --> 01:52:39.430
IS NEVER MORE THAN
TEMPORARY OR ILLUSORY.

01:52:39.430 --> 01:52:42.130
IN THE END, THE LOGIC
OF NATURE WILL WIN OUT

01:52:42.130 --> 01:52:47.160
OVER THE LOGIC OF CAPITALISM,
THE LOGIC OF THE FACTORY,

01:52:47.160 --> 01:52:49.730
IT'S ALWAYS BEEN SO AND
IT ALWAYS WILL BE SO.

01:52:49.730 --> 01:52:53.930
NATURE IS STRONGER THAN
ANY OF OUR DESIGNS.

01:52:53.930 --> 01:53:07.660
AND NATURE RESISTS OUR CONTROL.

01:53:07.660 --> 01:53:10.560
FOR ME, THE MOST
IMPORTANT LESSONS

01:53:10.560 --> 01:53:14.830
TO TAKE AWAY FROM THESE TALES
IS THAT WE ARE NOT SIMPLY

01:53:14.830 --> 01:53:17.560
STANDING OUTSIDE
THE WEB OF LIFE,

01:53:17.560 --> 01:53:20.260
BUT THAT WE ARE PART
OF THAT WEB OF LIFE

01:53:20.260 --> 01:53:22.000
AND THAT EVERYTHING WE DO --

01:53:22.000 --> 01:53:23.560
WHAT WE CHOOSE TO EAT,

01:53:23.560 --> 01:53:26.860
WHAT FLOWERS WE CHOOSE
TO PUT ON OUR TABLES,

01:53:26.860 --> 01:53:29.160
WHAT DRUGS WE CHOOSE TO TAKE --

01:53:29.160 --> 01:53:30.500
THESE ARE EVOLUTIONARY VOTES

01:53:30.500 --> 01:53:39.460
WE ARE CASTING EVERY DAY IN
MANY, MANY DIFFERENT WAYS.

01:53:39.460 --> 01:53:41.830
WHEN WE USE THESE
METAPHORS AND WE TALK

01:53:41.830 --> 01:53:44.500
ABOUT PLANTS HAVING
A STRATEGY TO DO THIS

01:53:44.500 --> 01:53:47.330
OR WANTING THIS
OR DESIRING THIS,

01:53:47.330 --> 01:53:49.260
WE'RE BEING
METAPHORICAL, OBVIOUSLY.

01:53:49.260 --> 01:53:51.600
I MEAN, PLANTS DO NOT
HAVE CONSCIOUSNESS.

01:53:51.600 --> 01:53:55.000
BUT THIS IS A FAULT
OF OUR OWN VOCABULARY.

01:53:55.000 --> 01:53:58.030
WE DON'T HAVE A VERY GOOD
VOCABULARY TO DESCRIBE

01:53:58.030 --> 01:54:01.030
WHAT OTHER SPECIES DO TO US
-- BECAUSE WE THINK WE'RE

01:54:01.030 --> 01:54:07.500
THE ONLY SPECIES THAT
REALLY DOES ANYTHING.

01:54:07.500 --> 01:54:10.900
BUT TO THE EXTENT THAT
YOU CAN PUT YOURSELF

01:54:10.900 --> 01:54:13.600
IN THE PLACE OF
THESE OTHER SPECIES

01:54:13.600 --> 01:54:15.560
AND LOOK AT THE WORLD
FROM THEIR POINT OF VIEW,

01:54:15.560 --> 01:54:19.630
I THINK IT FREES
US FROM OUR SENSE OF
ALIENATION FROM NATURE,

01:54:19.630 --> 01:54:23.260
AND WE BECOME MEMBERS
OF THE BIOTIC COMMUNITY,

01:54:23.260 --> 01:54:26.700
ONE AMONG MANY SPECIES,
ALL OF THEM TOGETHER

01:54:26.700 --> 01:54:40.160
CREATING THIS WONDROUS
WEB THAT WE CALL LIFE.

